This example exercises the TCPSocket and friends.

To run the server, open a command prompt, navigate to server/bin and type:

Windows:
thekogans_tcpecho_server-Windows-x86_64-cl-Release-Static.0.1.0.exe -c -l:Debug

Linux/OS X:
./thekogans_tcpecho_server-Windows-x86_64-cl-Release-Static.0.1.0 -c -l:Debug

To run the client, open a command prompt, navigate to client/bin and type:

Windows:
ipconfig
thekogans_tcpecho_client-Windows-x86_64-cl-Release-Static.0.1.0.exe -l:Debug -a:'address from ipconfig'

Linux/OS X:
ifconfig
./thekogans_tcpecho_client-Windows-x86_64-cl-Release-Static.0.1.0 -l:Debug -a:'address from ifconfig'
